#Text=Car bombings near Iraq government offices kill at least 130
#Text=Sunday , October 25 , 2009
#Text=At least 132 people were killed on Sunday after two car bombings struck the Iraqi capital of Baghdad .
#Text=Over 500 were hurt in the attacks , which were the worst to strike the country in over two years .
#Text=The attacks occurred at the Justice Ministry building and a provincial government office close to the high-security Green Zone part of the city .
#Text=The explosions came during rush hour , at 10.30 local time ( 07.30 UTC ) .
#Text=Officials have warned that the death toll is likely to rise , as rescue workers are still searching underneath the rubble of collapsed buildings to find more bodies .
#Text=Sources gave conflicting reports as to whether suicide bombers were involved in the attacks , or whether the bombs had been detonated remotely .
#Text=According to the police , cars loaded with explosives had been parked in garages close to the targeted buildings .
#Text=So many people were wounded in the blasts that private cars helped ambulances transport bodies to local hospitals .
#Text=Rescue efforts were hindered by the heavy rush hour traffic .
#Text=The buildings targeted by the bombings caught fire , and officials had to close down roads nearby as fire trucks tried to quell the flames .
#Text=Yasmeen Afdhal , 24 , who works for the Baghdad provincial administration , was a witness to one of the bombings .
#Text=He described his experiences : " the walls collapsed and we had to run out .

#Text= The explosion destroyed everything [ ... ] it 's like it was an earthquake , nothing is still in its place , " he said .

column1: #Text=A reporter for the BBC said that the force of the blast was so strong that it could be felt for several miles away .
#Text=Prime Minister Nouri Maliki accused al-Qaeda of being behind the bombings .

#Text=" These cowardly terrorist attacks must not affect the determination of the Iraqi people to continue their struggle against the remnants of the dismantled regime and al-Qaeda terrorists , who committed a brutal crime against civilians , " he said in a statement .
#Text=" They want to cause chaos in the nation , hinder the political process and prevent the parliamentary election .
